<item>
            <title>[SPARK-53549] Fix the list state memory leak issue due to an unclosed Arrow allocator</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-53549</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We create a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/7201e60bb3e898f65db5045ec293c650e14cfa95/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/execution/python/streaming/TransformWithStateInPySparkStateServer.scala#L460-L464&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;TransformWithStateInPySparkDeserializer&lt;/a&gt; every time when we process a list state request. Inside &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/execution/python/streaming/TransformWithStateInPySparkDeserializer.scala#L40&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;TransformWithStateInPySparkDeserializer&lt;/a&gt;, a child allocator is created from the &lt;b&gt;ArrowUtils.rootAllocator&lt;/b&gt; when a new deserializer instance is created. However, we neither close this child allocator nor call rootAllocator.close, which leads to a memory leak in TWSStateServer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
